  "title": "Introduction to Decorators",
  "lessonText": "Decorators are a powerful tool in Python that allow you to modify the behavior of functions or methods.",
  "data": {
    "content": "### Key Points\n- Decorators are functions that wrap another function.\n- They can add functionality to the original function.\n- Common use cases include logging, access control, and caching.\n- Syntax involves the `@decorator_name` notation above the function definition."
  }
}
